WEBVTT

00:00.258 --> 00:00.879
Good morning.

00:02.220 --> 00:05.343
The text for our meditation this morning comes to us from our gospel.

00:05.363 --> 00:07.165
Listen, let's begin with a word of prayer.

00:08.686 --> 00:19.317
Dear Heavenly Father, we thank you for this time where we gather together in faith under your invitation to be here to receive this morning the gift of a Savior.

00:20.778 --> 00:26.364
And for every Sunday we receive the gift of your word, of your sacrament given to us.

00:27.425 --> 00:28.466
We ask now that

00:28.546 --> 00:39.342
by the power of your Holy Spirit here among us that you would plant your word deeply within us, that it would guide our heart, our hearts, our thoughts, and our words and our actions as we go about assault and light in your kingdom.

00:39.362 --> 00:41.185
In the name of your son Jesus, we pray.

00:41.786 --> 00:42.106
Amen.

00:42.987 --> 00:43.648
Please be seated.

00:47.915 --> 00:51.380
Your brothers and sisters in Christ, this is the fourth day of Christmas.

00:52.742 --> 00:55.666
As we move closer to the epiphany of our Lord,

00:56.770 --> 01:03.622
It seems that our culture and society likes to cut Christmas off at 12 a.m. on December 26th.

01:04.463 --> 01:07.208
Of course, it begins like the day after Halloween.

01:09.732 --> 01:13.598
But as Christians, we love to linger on a bit.

01:14.580 --> 01:19.569
Kind of much like hanging around the dinner table after a special meal, like a Thanksgiving or Christmas.

01:19.629 --> 01:22.834
We all kind of hover and picket things until it's

01:23.586 --> 01:28.172
But we kind of like hanging around the Christmas season, even if it's for a short while.

01:29.574 --> 01:38.426
I have an interesting exchange with a person who in response to my insistence that the Christmas season, indeed, lasted the 12 days between Christmas and Epiphany.

01:39.387 --> 01:43.092
This person told me with great conviction, well, that is only in church time.

01:45.936 --> 01:53.266
I must admit I was taken aback a bit and was a bit incredulous when I responded, but we're celebrating the birth of Jesus Christ.

01:53.538 --> 01:54.579
Who is the church?

01:55.861 --> 01:56.042
Oi.

01:56.082 --> 02:02.871
And their response was something to the effect of, well, it's not that way in the real world.

02:04.113 --> 02:06.036
Another Oi and a slap of the head.

02:09.080 --> 02:11.703
But it is an event that we want to linger in.

02:11.764 --> 02:22.098
Taking in the manger scene, taking in all of kind of the trappings, taking in the image,

02:22.466 --> 02:25.931
of God coming down to us as someone we could recognize.

02:26.011 --> 02:41.576
As a baby, baby Jesus wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger surrounded by Mary and Joseph, shepherds, angels singing the glory in ex-jealous, glory to God in the highest.

02:43.579 --> 02:44.260
It's beautiful.

02:45.221 --> 02:45.822
It's peaceful.

02:46.944 --> 02:47.525
It's hopeful.

02:49.548 --> 02:50.930
It's a place we want to linger.

02:53.218 --> 03:01.488
The coming of Jesus into our world is undoubtedly the most positive and life-giving event in all of history.

03:03.190 --> 03:12.761
The greatest gift that God could give us was God Himself entering our flesh to save us from sin and death and the devil.

03:15.764 --> 03:17.426
Emmanuel, God with us.

03:18.754 --> 03:21.638
We sing it with longing and gusto and in advent.

03:21.658 --> 03:24.261
O come, O come, Emmanuel, God be with us, please.

03:27.125 --> 03:28.887
What could be better than lingering in that?

03:31.350 --> 03:39.821
But today's gospel reading from Matthew 2, in a way, kind of pulls back the curtain on the darker side of the story.

03:41.403 --> 03:44.127
Not everyone is happy about this birth of the Messiah.

03:44.167 --> 03:46.770
This Jesus, not everyone is happy about Christmas.

03:49.282 --> 03:51.364
Just read a little snippet from our gospel.

03:51.965 --> 04:04.416
When the wise men had departed, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in the dream and said, rise, take the child and his mother and flee to Egypt and remain there until I tell you, for Herod is about to search for the child to destroy him.

04:08.901 --> 04:14.506
And he rose and he took the child and his mother by night and departed to Egypt and remained there until the death of Herod.

04:14.926 --> 04:18.610
This was to fill what the Lord had spoken by the prophet out of Egypt.

04:19.010 --> 04:19.911
I called my son.

04:19.951 --> 04:24.938
Then Herod, when he saw that he had been tricked by the wise men, became furious.

04:26.440 --> 04:30.967
And he sent and killed all the male children in Bethlehem.

04:32.329 --> 04:44.386
And in all that region who were two years old or under, according to the time that he had ascertained from the wise men, then was fulfilled, what was spoken by the prophet Jeremiah.

04:45.587 --> 04:47.570
A voice was heard in Rama weeping.

04:48.066 --> 04:49.147
and law of lamentation.

04:50.308 --> 04:51.709
Rachel weeping for her children.

04:53.311 --> 04:55.613
She refused to be comforted because they are no more.

05:00.798 --> 05:06.824
This family, Mary Joseph and Jesus, were on the run.

05:06.864 --> 05:12.769
They became refugees, fleeing in the dead of night to a foreign land.

05:14.571 --> 05:17.714
While back in Bethlehem, innocent babies are slaughtered.

05:19.170 --> 05:32.286
simply because paranoid King Herod sees this newborn Jesus, this Messiah, it's King of the Jews, a threat to his own power.

05:36.851 --> 05:45.522
And our reading from Matthew emphasizes God's plan, a plan of action to protect and care for

05:45.730 --> 05:49.675
the one who is in danger, for the one who will ultimately save us from our sins.

05:51.538 --> 05:55.182
The humanity of Jesus is on full display, or he could be killed.

05:57.946 --> 05:58.827
Human, killed.

05:58.867 --> 06:01.411
There is a fear for his life.

06:08.059 --> 06:13.266
But as a plan unfolds, we are kind of moved quickly from the readings last week

06:13.890 --> 06:24.807
from serenity and joy of Christmas to that of Jesus in a very vulnerable state being carried through a world that is not receiving him.

06:26.710 --> 06:29.734
A world that is filled with opposition and violence.

06:32.779 --> 06:37.927
Violence even going so far as innocent children of Bethlehem being slaughtered.

06:38.888 --> 06:40.050
It's hard to even imagine.

06:44.098 --> 06:45.721
To every action, there is a reaction.

06:46.662 --> 06:54.134
The consequences of Christmas are severe, and they do not stop at Bethlehem.

06:54.154 --> 06:55.116
Not everyone is happy.

06:57.380 --> 06:58.201
Herod is furious.

06:59.363 --> 07:02.228
His throne feels like it's at risk, a little shaky.

07:02.268 --> 07:11.122
The king of the Jews, born in Bethlehem, challenges everything that Herod holds dear.

07:11.842 --> 07:15.568
loves his control, he loves his authority, he obviously loves his way of life.

07:18.473 --> 07:23.180
And so this light of Christ already is doing what it is supposed to do.

07:24.402 --> 07:26.426
And now it is to expose the darkness.

07:27.147 --> 07:33.718
And in this instance, the darkness that is in Herod's heart, in his being.

07:36.302 --> 07:38.866
And so Herod lashes out in rage.

07:43.138 --> 07:48.527
This is a consequence of Jesus coming down to us.

07:52.513 --> 07:58.222
When God enters our world in the person of Jesus, it is glorious news for those who receive Him.

07:59.785 --> 08:07.016
But it truly is a threat to those who love and cling to the darkness more than the light.

08:09.200 --> 08:10.642
The gospel divides.

08:12.770 --> 08:13.871
It brings resistance.

08:16.454 --> 08:18.216
It has a way of provoking opposition.

08:19.198 --> 08:20.539
And we see it in the world around us.

08:20.619 --> 08:25.064
We see it in our culture, in our society, in which we live, in the families we love.

08:27.768 --> 08:29.470
We see this pattern throughout scripture.

08:30.791 --> 08:40.082
Pharaoh tried to destroy the baby Moses because he feared of Israel growing, leading up to

08:40.834 --> 08:43.819
the powers of the world crucifying Jesus himself.

08:45.781 --> 08:52.992
And even after the resurrection, Jesus disciples facing persecution or proclaiming his name.

08:56.858 --> 09:07.314
But even today, not everyone is happy about the birth of Jesus and especially the people who believe as we do that he is the Son of God, the only way to the Father.

09:10.402 --> 09:13.407
That's a hard argument to get into sometimes around the dinner table.

09:15.089 --> 09:20.738
The message that we are sinners in need of a Savior offends our their pride.

09:23.041 --> 09:28.490
The call to repent and follow Christ challenges comfortable lives.

09:31.174 --> 09:39.186
The truth that Jesus is the only way to the Father threatens every human attempt to earn our salvation on our own terms, and we think we can.

09:40.898 --> 09:45.884
We think that somehow if we live good lives and treat people well, we have got it pretty much stowed up.

09:45.924 --> 09:54.594
It doesn't really matter if there's a God, if there's Jesus, what I believe, but as long as I treat people well, then I guess I'm doing a good enough job.

09:57.177 --> 10:01.783
But in our world, the gospel still meets resistance.

10:02.844 --> 10:07.730
In some places, Christians face persecution.

10:08.226 --> 10:13.911
churches burned, believers in prison killed, just look at what is happening in North Africa now.

10:16.854 --> 10:25.543
Just as those innocent children in Bethlehem really paid a price for only being in the proximity of the Christ child.

10:29.486 --> 10:34.311
Closer to home, the light of Christ exposes.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.394
It exposes sin and our culture.

10:38.818 --> 10:40.421
It exposes the sin in ourselves.

10:42.945 --> 10:48.114
All those things, greed, selfishness, immorality, the turning away from God.

10:53.523 --> 11:05.202
In our belief and for our faith, we often get the reaction of mockery, cancellation, and some laws that push our faith to the margins.

11:08.034 --> 11:09.416
And sometimes it feels like we're alone.

11:11.820 --> 11:12.561
And maybe we are.

11:12.701 --> 11:14.644
Maybe we are that last little remnant.

11:17.308 --> 11:33.311
And even in our hearts, there can be a little bit of that darkness of Herod where God's Word has a way of confronting our pet sins or calls us to sacrifice or calls us to change behaviors.

11:36.416 --> 11:37.938
Do we welcome it?

11:38.274 --> 11:43.060
Do we find a way to resist or rationalize, get angry, lash out?

11:46.724 --> 11:48.827
It certainly is a difficult text this morning.

11:51.430 --> 12:03.004
But the gospel, the good news part of this is that God's rule is sovereign overall and complete and will never end.

12:05.167 --> 12:08.050
Even over the resistance that we

12:08.642 --> 12:09.864
sometimes run into.

12:12.629 --> 12:13.410
He's got our back.

12:15.393 --> 12:16.836
He warns Joseph in a dream.

12:18.579 --> 12:19.600
He protects his son.

12:19.660 --> 12:23.747
He fulfills his promises through it all.

12:27.814 --> 12:31.520
Yeah, in that moment, Jesus escapes Herod's wrath.

12:33.724 --> 12:35.026
He escapes being slaughtered.

12:36.034 --> 13:01.938
Not that he's going to avoid suffering forever, but to face it later on the cross where he would take all of our sins, be sin himself and defeat sin and death once and for all, giving us not an optimism, but an assurance.

13:07.842 --> 13:16.650
I can't imagine being a parent back in that time in Bethlehem and seeing your child slaughtered.

13:20.034 --> 13:31.545
And the mothers and the fathers and the families didn't know it then, but the blood of their children pointed forward to the blood of the Lamb who would take away all the sins of the world.

13:33.286 --> 13:37.330
Jesus, who is the ultimate innocent

13:39.490 --> 13:45.398
would suffer so that no suffering or innocent suffering is meaningless.

13:47.361 --> 14:02.742
He comes to us, he enters our pain, and in the word of a hymn that escapes me now, he enters our poison air, our exile, our grief, and one day he will wipe away every tear.

14:05.987 --> 14:08.210
Rachel's weeping will turn to joy when

14:09.314 --> 14:15.122
We and all those who've gone before us rise in Christ.

14:17.805 --> 14:21.671
I don't think most of us want Christmas and it's a peaceful place to be.

14:21.731 --> 14:31.884
The coming of Jesus into our world is beautiful and positive infinitely, but it comes with consequences.

14:34.929 --> 14:38.994
There will be resistance to the gospel, what you believe, what I believe,

14:42.818 --> 14:44.641
There will be resistance to you.

14:44.681 --> 14:51.392
There will be resistance within your circle of friends and even your family.

14:54.978 --> 14:59.185
Jesus says in Matthew 10, anyone who loves your father or mother more than me is not worthy of me.

14:59.205 --> 15:03.431
Anyone who loves your son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.

15:05.935 --> 15:07.538
It's another ouch verse.

15:12.002 --> 15:18.812
But we love our families, but we also know that our ultimate allegiance and love goes to our Savior Jesus.

15:21.937 --> 15:28.466
And we take heart because we know, I say it a lot, how the story ends.

15:28.967 --> 15:30.609
The darkness cannot overcome the light.

15:30.649 --> 15:31.350
Jesus is one.

15:33.093 --> 15:36.658
He is with us in the fight in whatever we are up against.

15:38.722 --> 15:40.164
He's with us in the opposition.

15:40.264 --> 15:41.566
He's with us in the resistance.

15:41.666 --> 15:50.099
He's with us in those times where we're talking to people who are resisting us and we're simultaneously trying to say something and pray at the same time for words.

15:54.325 --> 15:56.909
And he will in the end bring us safely home to himself.

16:00.934 --> 16:06.162
I shared this passage yesterday with the family of Ralph, Domo, who is in ICU at Methodist Hospital.

16:08.578 --> 16:11.202
It comes from Paul's second letter to the Corinthians in chapter four.

16:14.207 --> 16:15.489
Therefore, we do not lose heart.

16:17.191 --> 16:26.285
Though outwardly we are wasting away, yet inwardly we are being renewed day by day, for our light and momentary troubles are achieving for us an eternal glory that far outweighs them all.

16:28.108 --> 16:34.298
So we fix our eyes not on what is seen, but on what is unseen.

16:35.520 --> 16:37.042
Since what is seen is temporary.

16:37.346 --> 16:39.769
But what is unseen is eternal.

16:42.433 --> 16:44.615
Folks, that is our assurance as Christians.

16:46.317 --> 16:49.862
The light we carry in Christ, the unseen things that in faith we rely.

16:49.902 --> 16:55.289
And yes, it attracts opposition, resentment, and even hatred.

16:58.113 --> 17:02.598
And so we shouldn't be surprised when not everyone is happy about Christmas.

17:04.881 --> 17:05.522
Instead,

17:07.330 --> 17:08.111
I need to.

17:08.652 --> 17:09.173
You need to.

17:09.333 --> 17:12.077
We need to cling to the one who came for us.

17:13.159 --> 17:14.381
We trust His protection.

17:16.464 --> 17:25.178
We boldly share the light that is ours through Him and the gospel that saves even when it may cost us.

17:26.720 --> 17:35.634
Because in the end, every knee will bow and every tongue will confess that Jesus Christ is Lord.

17:37.378 --> 17:41.710
the peace of God which surpasses all understanding, guard your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.

17:42.617 --> 17:43.060
Amen.

